    sections: [
      { heading: "Honest Arithmetic", body: "Roster travel standards are built from evidence and maintained against drift. The baseline: mapping-tool estimates for every recurring journey pair, corrected by local knowledge (parking reality, one-way systems, the door-to-door walk at each end — the journey is doorstep to doorstep, not kerb to kerb) and validated against ECM gap data, which records what journeys actually take across hundreds of repetitions. The adjustments: time-of-day bands (peak school-run and commute corrections), day-type (market day in the market town), season (winter global uplift, rural daylight weighting), and mode (each worker's actual transport). The floor rules: minimum travel allowances between non-adjacent calls that the rostering system physically enforces (the coordinator cannot book the impossible without an override that names itself in the audit trail), zero-travel permitted only for same-site pairs, and run-length maximums that keep the day's arithmetic inside working-time and human reality. Standards are reviewed on the analytics cycle and when the geography changes (the new bypass, the closed bridge, the new client cluster). And the design honesty extends to acceptance decisions: a referral whose postcode and time-band the service cannot reach without fiction is negotiated (different time window) or declined — taking undeliverable work is how travel fiction enters the roster wearing growth's clothes." },
      { heading: "Pay, Working Time and the Law's Floor", body: "The pay treatment is written where every worker can read it: travel time between assignments paid (per the service's model — actual time, standardised allowances, or salaried arrangements — but paid, and demonstrably so), mileage reimbursed at the stated rate with a claim process that pays promptly and doesn't make workers subsidise the service's fuel, and the National Minimum Wage arithmetic done properly: across each pay reference period, total pay divided by total working time — including travel between calls, which the law counts — meets or exceeds NMW, with the calculation audited periodically and after pay or roster model changes, because care providers fail this test chronically and the failures are both unlawful and discovered eventually. Working time protections ride alongside: rest breaks rostered realistically within long runs (the break that exists only on paper because travel ate it is a working-time failure), daily rest respected between late finishes and early starts (the 10pm-to-7am turnaround is watched), and the fatigue interface with safe driving (hr-021/hr-025) treated as the safety-critical loop it is: tired driving between calls is work-related road risk, and the roster is its first cause or first control. Where workers use public transport or walk, the same principles translate: journey time is working time between assignments, and the standards reflect the mode's reality." },
      { heading: "The Drive Itself", body: "Work driving standards compress into one sentence — legal, safe, and never traded for the schedule — and the policy builds the supports that make the sentence true. Vehicle gateway per ch-010: business-use insurance (the commuting-only policy voids on the first work journey between calls), licence verification on cycle, roadworthiness declared with MOT/service honesty, and the declined-to-drive option always available (the worker whose car died serves a walking or paired run while it's fixed, not a guilt trip). Behavioural absolutes per hr-025: no handheld use ever, hands-free minimised, navigation set before moving, and the office culture audited against its own rules — the coordinator who phones a driving worker and expects an answer is the policy's saboteur. The pressure valve stated in policy terms: late-because-safe is always defensible, lateness from honest travel is escalated as roster data not worker failing, and any manager found pressuring speed (explicitly or by arithmetic) answers for it. Weather protocols: the winter uplift applied by date not debate; severe-weather days triaged on dc-003's criticality (reds prioritised and bridged, ambers sequenced by need, greens rescheduled with communication), the pre-mapped assets deployed (4x4 owners, walkable local pairings, family bridges), and the stand-down call made centrally with alternative coverage arranged — the service never outsources the do-I-risk-the-ice decision to individual workers' consciences. Breakdown and incident: hr-026's net covers the stranded worker, the coordinator redistributes the run by criticality, and the incident machinery captures anything reportable." },
      { heading: "Watching the Fiction Indicators", body: "Travel fiction announces itself in patterns before it announces itself in tragedy, and the monthly analytics read for its signatures. The direct measures: ECM gap analysis versus rostered allowances per journey pair (systematic shortfalls fixed at the standard, not the worker); lateness cascades traced to their arithmetic origin (the run that fails at the same junction of calls daily); call-length erosion correlated with run position (calls clipped at run's end are travel debt being paid by clients); and mileage claims versus rostered geography (divergences meaning unrecorded journeys or wrong maps). The human measures: worker feedback actively gathered (the run review question in supervision: 'which journeys don't work?'), turnover and exit themes read for schedule pressure, and complaint patterns (the 'always late' complaints clustering on one run are a design confession). The responses are structural in order of honesty: rebuild the run (resequence, recluster, add travel), adjust the standards (the map was wrong), add capacity (the geography needs another worker), renegotiate or return work (the commissioned volume exceeds physics — put to the commissioner in writing with the data, because a service that silently absorbs undeliverable volume is choosing clipped calls on its clients' behalf). Governance sees the travel-honesty picture quarterly alongside dc-003's reliability data — the two are one system: the roster's arithmetic is the safety net's foundation, and every fiction in the first is a hole in the second." },
    ],
